Check the path location where Python was installed along with its version. 
C:\Users\admin>py -m pip --version

Upgrade and Install pip 
C:\Users\admin>py -m pip install --upgrade pip

Install Numpy: 
C:\Users\admin>py -m pip install numpy

Install Pandas: 
C:\Users\admin>py -m pip install pandas

Install Matplotlib 
C:\Users\admin>py -m pip install matplotlib

In order to Install Jupyter Notebook on desktop, copy the path of main python folder and path of script folder inside python folder from c-drive program files and paste it on environment variables on desktop.
Now open command prompt and enter pip install jupyter notebook. 
Then type python -m notebook on command prompt. 
